column5: Congrats on the new fishin partner, Chris may have a life jacket for him. Brooks was getting to small
YA, what Dave said. Please note that an auto-inflate would be a bad choice. Lifting his little leg for relief only to have the PFD trigger would cause him to not pee for a year.
Cute pup.......love the ears...  Life Jacket ? ? ?  all you need is a large bobber attached to the collar...
Life jacket? I've seen what happens when Joey sets the hook or tries to lift a fish into the boat. I think a "life jacket" for him would be a full body Kevlar suit with safety glasses.  :tease:
LOL....I put Brook on a diet and she's now good with her life jacket.
Musky Bait.   Congrat's on the new pooch Joey!
Wow, you guys don't waste any time. Cute pup!
Naaaa definitely Roy's eyes. Congrat's guys he's much cuter than Paul!

Thanks everyone, and for the suggestions to knit him a firetiger sweater  He's doing very well and slept from midnight to 6 a.m.  I thought that was pretty good. He's eating, drinking, pooping, peeing and playing, so things look to be in order.  Alot of laughs already with the little guy.  Cheers!
Or lunch maybe for Digger...
Congratulations guys! He is SWEET!
Very nice!! TAwnia, my better half says you will have to make him (or her) some sweaters for in the boat, during the cooler weather..
Congrats Joey. I'm sure that he will be a great fishing companion! Enjoy.
Very nice pup, I guess that makes Paul   Iggy Pop   lol
Congrets.  Cute little pup!
~~~~Great looken pup
Just remember to feed the wee fella fish twice a week.
OMG Cuties Frenchie. My Lady wants one so bad
Wow what a cutie pie for sure and the dog ain't bad looking either

I would add an orange belly to Iggy and you'd be all set for the Kawartha skies. Maybe Roy could do a bit of a custom job for ya the next time you see him.	LOL! I'm kidding as well, figured it wouldn't take you long to get the new addition to the family. Enjoy!
nice looking pup joey congrats just picked up my new pup 3 weeks ago
LOL.....sorry Joey......i have been calling your pup 'Ralphie' for months...weird.  Sorry Iggy!
Here is the new addition to our family, Iggy, our new fishing partner          Thanks again for all your tips and help.  Really exciting time here in the Tyborski household
Awwwwwwww.......very cute!  Congrats you two!
good colour for Kawartha muskie      LOL  you know I am kidding   cute pup
What a sweety.You made Betty say AAAAAWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWWW.LOL
OMG !!!!!!!!!!! He`s so dang cute !!!!!!  Congrats on the new addition to your familly. Has Roys ears though
Very nice glad to see the new addition to the OFC.   Art
A newbie puppy , Joey you got to get him a membership on here , ruff ruff would mean meter swales in his post .Happy fishing with your new little friend .
Alright, what the heck kinda 'Dawg' is that???
BOSTON TERRIER SOOOO CUUUUUTE
I AM HAPPY FOR U:clapping::   I:rolleyes:
My dad's favorite breed of dog...  Word of warning:  They are the fartingest breed...Paul can blame the dog now...
Actually, it is a French Bulldog!!  Thanks all, he's napping now
Iggy..god that's a great name Joey  Enjoy your little bundle of joy.
What a cute little bundle  May your adventures be many. maybe Iggy and Peanut will cross paths one day.
Absolutely adorable!!!!!  You're gonna have tonnes of fun

Well I am shocked I get to be the first to say it MUSKY BAIT!!! for the better of teh hound the first time he poops in the boat he had better hope its after Dec15th or before June 2nd next year.  Very cute Joey and the dog looks good also (sorry Roy I had to)
Puppies are awesome,until you come home to this.

I have freinds with two just like that. One of them was nearly taken away by an owl at our cottage one night. Just something to think about.  They are great little dogs, I'm sure you will enjoy his company!!  S.
Gee, thanks for that Drifter
Good luck pup. I'm sure he'll bring fish to the boat. Have fun with Iggy Pop for the next few years
Who doesn't love a puppy ??  Congrats Joey, you've got a new best friend for many years now !!
What a beauty (pup is pretty cute too)!  Have fun with your new addition Joey, that is one lucky pup!
Another Lakair playmate for the dog pack.

I learned something from this thread. I think I just learned the way to Joey's heart.  Congratulations Hon. Oh and to you too, Paul. If I can offer one piece of advice...leave only Paul's stuff out in the open for the first few months as the little guy will need to practice his chewing skills.  Really happy for you both here.  Can't wait to see him reel in his first muskie!!!!
congrats on the new furry kid Joey. one question. As i am a musky fishermen does thet breed come with rattles or not.  enjoy the many years of fun.
